@StormLiangMS The duplicate `-iu` rendering is an existing configuration defect. A VLAN with primary and secondary prefixes is currently emitted more than once in the upstream-interface list.

For `dhcpmon`, each duplicate argument increments the upstream-interface count and allocates another device context for the same name; the second registration overwrites and leaks the first context, so interface registration and monitoring bookkeeping are incorrect. For ISC `dhcrelay`, duplicate upstream registrations create duplicate receive sockets and can double-forward a server reply.

The same erroneous template behavior exists in 202605, which is why the backport is requested. I updated the PR title and description to make the failure mechanism and backport reason explicit. The target-branch validation is still listed as pending rather than claimed complete.
